laboratory_examinations.findings: New Q wave noted on the electrocardiogram after myocardial infarction.
Elevated to 110 IU/L after myocardial infarction.
Postoperative echocardiogram showed satisfactory LVEF (56%). Readmission echocardiogram showed severe left ventricular dysfunction with LVEF of 35%.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: LVEF declined from 56% to 35% over 42 days.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Both grafts were patent, but new tight stenoses were found upstream and downstream from the LITA-LAD anastomosis and upstream from the RSV-RCA anastomosis; also a 30% stenosis downstream.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: New tight stenoses developed 42 days after the initial surgery.
